@node "history" "Frodo - History"

 Rev 1 -000220
       -First revision, most features working.

 Rev 2 -000226
       -Added two player support using joystick + keyboard.
       -One can now swap the joystick ports using the '.' key on the keypad.
       -Forced joystick with lowlevel.library to try and fix the problems reported with
        single button joysticks.

 Rev 3 -000308
       -Pressing ENTER on the keypad now brings up a requester letting you change the
        disk in drive 8.
       -000311
       -One can now use two joysticks for two player support. Please remember that if
        you use this mode with the mouse plugged in, you are very likely to get really
        strange effects!

 Rev 4 -000314
       -Now uses timing to try and give the right framerate on fast computers.
       -000406
       -Recompiled with EGCS 2.95.2 instead of old GCC 2.7.2.1. Should be a bit faster.
       -000527
       -Frodo will now remember the path of the last loaded file using the ASL requester.
       -000620
       -Added NOTIMER switch, might be usefull on slow CPU's.


@endnode
